[{"id":"VH967126","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a conducting shell with a charge of positive 5 Q. A point charge, positive Q, is located in the center if the conducting shell.\" height=\"241\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH967126.g02.png\" width=\"275\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A spherical conducting shell has a net charge of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive 5 Q\"><math alttext=\"positive 5 Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mtext>Q</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. At the center of the shell, there is a point charge of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>+Q</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, as shown in the figure. Which of the following gives the charge on the inner surface of the shell and provides evidence to support this claim?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH967126_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative Q\"><math alttext=\"negative Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>−</mo><mtext>Q</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because the electric field inside the conducting shell is zero.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative Q\"><math alttext=\"negative Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mrow><mo>−</mo><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Q</mtext></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mrow></math></span></span>, because the electric potential inside the conducting shell is zero.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive 5 Q\"><math alttext=\"positive 5 Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mtext>Q</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because the electric field inside the conducting shell is zero.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive 5 Q\"><math alttext=\"positive 5 Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mtext>Q</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because the electric potential inside the conducting shell is zero.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive 6 Q\"><math alttext=\"positive 6 Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mtext>Q</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because the electric field inside the conducting shell is zero.</p>"],"answer":0}]